## ü§ñ UI Framework: shadcn/ui (v2.1)

To standardize our component library and accelerate development, we now use **`shadcn/ui`**. This is a significant change from our previous approach.

- **Core Principle**: `shadcn/ui` is not a traditional component library. It provides source code that we copy into our project, giving us full control.
- **Installation**: `npx shadcn@latest init`
- **Configuration**: See `components.json` for path aliases (`@/components`, `@/lib/utils`).
- **Adding Components**: Add new components via `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]`. They will be added to `components/ui`.

