## üé® Brand Tokens (v2.1)

### Colors (via CSS HSL Variables)
The `shadcn/ui` integration introduces a new, semantic color system using HSL variables defined in `:root` within `app/globals.css`. **This is the new standard.**

```css
/* Example from app/globals.css */
:root {
  --background: 0 0% 95.7%; /* Mapped to sovira-paper */
  --foreground: 0 0% 6.7%;  /* Mapped to sovira-black */
  --primary: 240 57.9% 62.6%; /* Mapped to sovira-chartreuse-readable */
  --accent: 75 100% 50%;      /* Mapped to sovira-chartreuse */
  /* ... and other shadcn variables for borders, inputs, etc. */
}
```

**Usage Guidelines**:
- **Application**: Always prefer Tailwind's semantic classes (`bg-background`, `text-primary`, `border-accent`) over direct color classes like `bg-sovira-paper`. This makes our theming more robust.
- **Global Selection Highlight**: The browser's text selection highlight is globally styled to use `sovira-chartreuse` for a branded feel. This is configured in `app/globals.css`.
  ```css
  ::selection {
    background: #C6FF00; /* var(--accent) */
    color: #111111;      /* var(--foreground) */
  }
  ```

### Usage guidelines
- Declare the palette once in **`tailwind.config.ts`** under `theme.extend.colors`.
- Use `bg-sovira-*`, `text-sovira-*`, `border-sovira-*`; opacity variants are generated automatically (`/50`, `/70`, etc.).
- Maintain **WCAG AA (4.5 : 1)** contrast; prefer `text-sovira-paper` on dark surfaces.
- **Color Strategy for Readability**:
  - Use `text-sovira-chartreuse` for glow effects and elements on dark backgrounds
  - Use `text-sovira-chartreuse-readable` for text and icons on white/light backgrounds
  - The readable variant (#6564DB) provides excellent contrast while maintaining brand cohesion
- Gradients  
  - Accent ‚Üí Black: `bg-sovira-gradient-accent` (`from-sovira-chartreuse via-transparent to-sovira-black`)  
  - Graphite overlay: `bg-sovira-gradient-dark`

### Chartreuse Implementation Strategy (v2.1 - Implemented)
**Problem Solved**: Original chartreuse (#C6FF00) was difficult to read on white backgrounds.

**Solution**: Dual-color system maintaining brand identity while improving accessibility.

| Context | Color Token | Usage |
|---------|-------------|--------|
| **Glow effects** | `sovira-chartreuse` | Background glow, overlays, dark sections |
| **Text on white** | `sovira-chartreuse-readable` | Checkmarks, highlights, hover states |
| **Background elements** | `sovira-chartreuse` | Buttons, badges, non-text elements |

**Implementation Examples**:
```typescript
// ‚úÖ Glow effects - keep original chartreuse
<span className="absolute inset-0 blur-3xl bg-sovira-chartreuse opacity-25" />

// ‚úÖ Text on white backgrounds - use readable variant
<span className="text-sovira-chartreuse-readable">‚úì</span>

// ‚úÖ Conditional usage based on background
<span className={`${tier.popular ? 'text-sovira-chartreuse-readable' : 'text-sovira-chartreuse'}`}>‚úì</span>
