## üèóÔ∏è Implemented Component Patterns (v2.1)

### Responsive Comparison Table (`components/ComparisonTable.tsx`)
**Requirement**: The table must be perfectly readable on all devices without horizontal scrolling.

**Implementation**:
- **Desktop**: A standard three-column layout using `shadcn/ui`'s `<Table>` component. Key rows are highlighted with a subtle background color (`bg-sovira-paper/[.03]`) and increased vertical padding (`py-8`) for a premium feel.
- **Mobile**: The layout transforms into a stacked card view. Each feature is presented in its own card, with "Traditional" and "Sovira" values displayed side-by-side. This is achieved by conditionally rendering the layouts using `md:hidden` and `hidden md:block`.

```typescript
// Desktop Layout (hidden on mobile)
<div className="hidden md:block">
  <Table> ... </Table>
</div>

// Mobile Layout (hidden on desktop)
<div className="md:hidden">
  {items.map(item => (
    <div className="p-4 rounded-lg bg-sovira-paper/5">
      {/* Mobile card structure */}
    </div>
  ))}
</div>
```
This pattern is our standard for presenting complex data on different screen sizes.

